<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dfa21d9694b80a2f89acbe14ca29d007 sig_cn_org=1107c385f7ecef14603d983a5b7743ff source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix inadequate validation of multibyte character lengths
      (Thomas Munro, Noah Misch)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;df0852fe0">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;efef05ba9">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7b5fc85be">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b0f5d25bc">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b42709194">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;4543b02af">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复多字节字符长度的验证不足问题
      （Thomas Munro，Noah Misch）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;df0852fe0">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;efef05ba9">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7b5fc85be">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b0f5d25bc">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b42709194">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;4543b02af">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dfa21d9694b80a2f89acbe14ca29d007 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5f0729aa715613bbf506cb628bf2b02d sig_cn_org=a87e673eafece0af3d6dda1b0255165e source=18.3 
     <para>
      Assorted bugs allowed an attacker able to issue crafted SQL to
      overrun string buffers, with consequences as bad as arbitrary code
      execution.  After these fixes, applications may
      observe <quote>invalid byte sequence for encoding</quote> errors
      when string functions process invalid text that has been stored in
      the database.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      各种错误允许攻击者通过发出精心构造的 SQL
      来溢出字符串缓冲区，后果严重，可能导致任意代码
      执行。修复后，应用程序可能会
      观察到 <quote>编码的无效字节序列</quote> 错误
      当字符串函数处理存储在数据库中的无效文本时。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5f0729aa715613bbf506cb628bf2b02d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6b93990cd11533cb827bee0775acdef2 sig_cn_org=39129b7f914d0475e56bc8e89701e782 source=18.3 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks Paul Gerste
      and Moritz Sanft, as part of zeroday.cloud, for reporting this
      problem.
      (CVE-2026-2006)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 项目感谢 Paul Gerste
      和 Moritz Sanft，作为 zeroday.cloud 的一部分，报告了此
      问题。
      （CVE-2026-2006）
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6b93990cd11533cb827bee0775acdef2 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [00896ddaf] 2026-02-09 12:08:58 +1300
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [e0965fb1a] 2026-02-09 12:12:24 +1300
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [54598670f] 2026-02-09 12:08:58 +1300
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [18548681d] 2026-02-09 12:12:18 +1300
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8d18d2837656bfe5ea965ae7ee7a845b sig_cn_org=507adab1e6979c2e40d2b5d436a70ad4 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Harden <filename>contrib/pg_trgm</filename> against changes in
      string lowercasing behavior (Heikki Linnakangas)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e0965fb1a">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;18548681d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      加强 <filename>contrib/pg_trgm</filename> 对字符串小写行为变化的
      保护（Heikki Linnakangas）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e0965fb1a">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;18548681d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8d18d2837656bfe5ea965ae7ee7a845b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7ddac8e65ffb5ef681467d8ee54b1d29 sig_cn_org=8d23538bc9a33beb4cb9274b1de15401 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix potential buffer overruns arising from the fact that in some
      locales lower-casing a string can produce more characters (not
      bytes) than were in the original.  That behavior is new in version
      18, and so is the bug.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复由于某些区域设置中小写字符串可能产生的字符数
      （而不是字节）超过原始字符数而导致的潜在缓冲区溢出。
      这种行为在版本 18 中是新的，错误也是如此。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7ddac8e65ffb5ef681467d8ee54b1d29 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=2fda7a5553ff7a041077a937f77c585c sig_cn_org=315dc540d7a556a6ffe05f24ada98ebf source=18.3 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Heikki Linnakangas for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2026-2007)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 项目感谢
      Heikki Linnakangas 报告了此问题。
      （CVE-2026-2007）
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=2fda7a5553ff7a041077a937f77c585c -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Jeff Davis <jdavis@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [7f007e4a0] 2025-12-16 12:57:00 -0800
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [806555e30] 2025-12-16 12:57:12 -0800
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [8993bf099] 2026-01-27 08:16:07 -0800
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5b1d91f8ecf6e79d5958cc9b3963264e sig_cn_org=3cc46ee4436f3e02552e299948752499 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix inconsistent case-insensitive matching
      in <filename>contrib/ltree</filename> (Jeff Davis)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;806555e30">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;8993bf099">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复 <filename>contrib/ltree</filename> 中不一致的大小写不敏感匹配
      （Jeff Davis）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;806555e30">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;8993bf099">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5b1d91f8ecf6e79d5958cc9b3963264e -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=aef531efc39abc9b1c6431374e7a0add sig_cn_org=b95413aa6d224924832178f95cdbcf49 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Index-related routines in <filename>ltree</filename> used a
      different implementation of case-folding than the primary operators
      did.  Their behavior was equivalent only if the default collation
      provider was libc and the encoding was single-byte.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <filename>ltree</filename> 中与索引相关的例程使用了
      与主运算符不同的大小写折叠实现。
      只有在默认排序提供者为 libc 且编码为单字节时，它们的行为才是等效的。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=aef531efc39abc9b1c6431374e7a0add -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=2fee9dec3cfa9128ce69ac1d75806319 sig_cn_org=ae66cf286add23e001739d36aa83fd25 source=18.3 
     <para>
      To fix, change the code to use case-folding with the database's
      default collation.
      This change will require reindexing indexes on <type>ltree</type>
      columns (regardless of the index access method) unless the database
      uses libc as collation provider and its encoding is single-byte.
      Without that, searches of such indexes will fail to locate relevant
      entries.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      为了解决此问题，请更改代码以使用数据库的
      默认排序进行大小写折叠。
      此更改将要求重新索引 <type>ltree</type> 列上的索引
      （无论索引访问方法如何），除非数据库使用 libc 作为排序提供者且其编码为单字节。
      否则，搜索此类索引将无法找到相关条目。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=2fee9dec3cfa9128ce69ac1d75806319 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Álvaro Herrera <alvherre@kurilemu.de>
Branch: master [96e2af605] 2026-02-03 12:33:29 +0100
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [492a69e14] 2026-02-03 12:33:29 +0100
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=92e33a01ca536a6f4692159fb4e93ac0 sig_cn_org=a74f2b3cd1e7a98d06fd3af5dfe3b3d8 source=18.3 
     <para>
      When using <command>ALTER TABLE ... ADD CONSTRAINT</command> to add
      a not-null constraint with an explicit name, if the column is
      already marked NOT NULL, require that the provided name match the
      existing constraint name (Álvaro Herrera, Srinath Reddy Sadipiralla)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;492a69e14">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      当使用 <command>ALTER TABLE ... ADD CONSTRAINT</command> 添加
      显式名称的非空约束时，如果列已经标记为 NOT NULL，
      则要求提供的名称与现有约束名称匹配
      （Álvaro Herrera，Srinath Reddy Sadipiralla）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;492a69e14">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=92e33a01ca536a6f4692159fb4e93ac0 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
Branch: master [35b5c62c3] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [12bc32917] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [075a763e2] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [1c8c3206f] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [9f5a58aac] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [b85397481] 2025-11-18 12:56:55 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=abcf5608c8950d228043f91cae975697 sig_cn_org=d95413e7826a1eaa6a7260f2e757c7c0 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Don't allow CTE references in sub-selects to determine semantic
      levels of aggregate functions (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;12bc32917">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      不允许在子查询中引用 CTE 来确定聚合函数的语义
      级别（Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;12bc32917">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=abcf5608c8950d228043f91cae975697 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3a1e8800f2c829ce9dfaeca6703cfc81 sig_cn_org=8c130a31b948aa6d8dbead8cbdd5f84b source=18.3 
     <para>
      This change undoes a change made two minor releases ago, instead
      throwing an error if a sub-select references a CTE that's below the
      semantic level that standard SQL rules would assign to the aggregate
      based on contained column references and aggregates.  The attempted
      fix turned out to cause problems of its own, and it's unclear what
      to do instead.  Since sub-selects within aggregates are disallowed
      altogether by the SQL standard, treating such cases as errors seems
      sufficient.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此更改撤销了两个小版本之前所做的更改，如果子查询引用了
      一个低于标准 SQL 规则所分配给基于包含列引用和聚合的
      聚合的语义级别的 CTE，则会抛出错误。尝试的修复结果
      导致了自身的问题，目前尚不清楚该如何处理。由于 SQL
      标准完全不允许在聚合内使用子查询，因此将此类情况视为
      错误似乎是足够的。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3a1e8800f2c829ce9dfaeca6703cfc81 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Dean Rasheed <dean.a.rasheed@gmail.com>
Branch: master [b4307ae2e] 2026-01-24 11:30:48 +0000
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [c6ce4dcf9] 2026-01-24 11:30:48 +0000
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [c5fc17dda] 2026-01-24 11:30:49 +0000
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [e7391bbf1] 2026-01-24 11:30:50 +0000
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [c5824536e] 2026-01-24 11:30:51 +0000
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c1a2a53987729808ceedc14988a56c81 sig_cn_org=c3e71c24bcbfeb6af844c69a448976bb source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix trigger transition table capture for <command>MERGE</command>
      in CTE queries (Dean Rasheed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c6ce4dcf9">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复 CTE 查询中 <command>MERGE</command> 的触发器过渡表捕获
      （Dean Rasheed）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c6ce4dcf9">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c1a2a53987729808ceedc14988a56c81 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a99e45555447016aa2ec3842bcb0346c sig_cn_org=26605b95d5db27e2d35bb284f9ef3483 source=18.3 
     <para>
      When executing a data-modifying CTE query containing both
      a <command>MERGE</command> and another DML operation on a table with
      statement-level <literal>AFTER</literal> triggers, the transition
      tables passed to the triggers would not include the rows affected by
      the <command>MERGE</command>, only those affected by the other
      operation(s).
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      当执行包含 <command>MERGE</command> 和其他 DML 操作的
      数据修改 CTE 查询时，如果该表具有语句级 <literal>AFTER</literal>
      触发器，则传递给触发器的过渡表将不包括受 <command>MERGE</command>
      影响的行，仅包括受其他操作影响的行。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a99e45555447016aa2ec3842bcb0346c -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Amit Langote <amitlan@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [889676a0d] 2026-01-16 14:53:50 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [f335457e8] 2026-01-16 14:53:32 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dc49a467cddb80ef36c9844ac929320d sig_cn_org=a8b1e5595bd9284433dca4b8c917d86f source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix incorrect pruning of rowmarks belonging to non-relation
      rangetable entries, such as subqueries (Dean Rasheed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f335457e8">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复属于非关系范围表条目的行标记的错误修剪，例如子查询
      （Dean Rasheed）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f335457e8">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dc49a467cddb80ef36c9844ac929320d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=616925c581d13826bedd99ba7cf6f650 sig_cn_org=76b7ca3d404888ca714cb5867335526d source=18.3 
     <para>
      This led to incorrect results if a proposed row update needed to be
      modified by EvalPlanQual rechecking, as could happen if there was a
      concurrent update to that row.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      如果提议的行更新需要通过 EvalPlanQual 重新检查进行修改，
      则会导致不正确的结果，因为可能会发生对该行的并发更新。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=616925c581d13826bedd99ba7cf6f650 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Amit Langote <amitlan@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [f9a468c66] 2026-01-23 10:23:30 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [9f4b7bfc5] 2026-01-23 10:23:26 +0900
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [933f67fb6] 2026-01-23 10:23:22 +0900
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [fab386f74] 2026-01-23 10:23:18 +0900
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [687533b39] 2026-01-23 10:23:14 +0900
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [6d2fa44d2] 2026-01-23 10:23:10 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=768ea8bea2ab7a8d4b737bd015421403 sig_cn_org=8726dc5c65f068f1a324db07a661c61b source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix failure when all children of a partitioned target table
      of an update or delete have been pruned (Amit Langote)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9f4b7bfc5">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复当更新或删除的分区目标表的所有子表都被修剪时的失败
      （Amit Langote）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9f4b7bfc5">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=768ea8bea2ab7a8d4b737bd015421403 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=2a518123bdd0107cd4ea8be5cb7bc76d sig_cn_org=db262009c366ed2d89a5d8789fd501cb source=18.3 
     <para>
      In such cases, the executor could report <quote>could not find junk
      ctid column</quote> errors, even though nothing needs to be done.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在这种情况下，执行器可能会报告 <quote>找不到垃圾 ctid 列</quote>
      错误，即使实际上不需要执行任何操作。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=2a518123bdd0107cd4ea8be5cb7bc76d -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Andres Freund <andres@anarazel.de>
Branch: master [75609fded] 2026-01-06 19:51:10 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [bdc5dedfc] 2026-01-06 19:51:19 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c8693ac16a0a92957aaf991b614771ec sig_cn_org=d38dc5141ac9b0a95c685f12770f7df2 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix expression evaluation bug for a sub-select within an array
      subscript (Andres Freund)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bdc5dedfc">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复数组下标内子查询的表达式评估错误（Andres Freund）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bdc5dedfc">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c8693ac16a0a92957aaf991b614771ec -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
Branch: master [6dfce8420] 2025-12-05 20:10:33 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [18b349315] 2025-12-05 20:10:33 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d4418315444574e5526c191920afc988 sig_cn_org=be7a80a1a4aa2bc2398ed4fb69c541c2 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix text substring search for non-deterministic collations
      (Laurenz Albe)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;18b349315">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复非确定性排序规则下的文本子字符串搜索（Laurenz Albe）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;18b349315">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d4418315444574e5526c191920afc988 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f89d74a2345d90e49ebe00a9525c3af8 sig_cn_org=2902941eac1ede0ce376d34b89a0a675 source=18.3 
     <para>
      When using a non-deterministic collation, we failed to detect a
      match occurring at the very end of the searched string.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      当使用非确定性排序规则时，我们未能检测到在搜索字符串的
      最后位置发生的匹配。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f89d74a2345d90e49ebe00a9525c3af8 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [7027dd499] 2026-01-26 23:27:15 +1300
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [ccde5be68] 2026-01-26 23:46:23 +1300
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [cae812741] 2026-01-26 23:47:07 +1300
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [4297a3519] 2026-01-26 23:47:37 +1300
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=15bcab6b0e9f07ceacb9a2af84fbe380 sig_cn_org=8b743165cb32585ccdba33cd9d17f880 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Avoid possible planner failure when a query contains duplicate
      window function calls (Meng Zhang, David Rowley)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ccde5be68">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      当查询包含重复的窗口函数调用时，避免可能的规划器失败
      （Meng Zhang, David Rowley）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ccde5be68">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=15bcab6b0e9f07ceacb9a2af84fbe380 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0fb60abf43d3b5ab7a18b69d41fe535f sig_cn_org=9d61c82743f4d24221d66790e0d0bf37 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Confusion over de-duplication of such calls could result in errors
      like <quote>WindowFunc with winref 2 assigned to WindowAgg with
      winref 1</quote>.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      对此类调用的去重混淆可能导致错误，例如 <quote>窗口函数
      winref 2 被分配给窗口聚合 winref 1</quote>。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0fb60abf43d3b5ab7a18b69d41fe535f -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [325808cac] 2025-12-25 12:12:52 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [382ce9cb7] 2025-12-25 12:15:09 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7d4d8dec97c5c1ed4661b13c82161d28 sig_cn_org=7ac9367a2d8080fa4615852cd2d17845 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix planner error with set-returning functions and grouping sets
      (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;382ce9cb7">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复与返回集合的函数和分组集相关的规划器错误
      （Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;382ce9cb7">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7d4d8dec97c5c1ed4661b13c82161d28 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=bb65224aa214d11206ec63e55b3b560e sig_cn_org=c3238b08eb45c92fa6ed3ab9cbb83957 source=18.3 
     <para>
      When constructing a ProjectSet plan node, the planner failed to
      detect that subexpressions involving grouping expressions were
      already computed by the input plan.  This led to inefficient plans
      or errors such as <quote>variable not found in subplan target
      list</quote>.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在构造 ProjectSet 计划节点时，规划器未能检测到涉及分组
      表达式的子表达式已经由输入计划计算。这导致了低效的计划
      或错误，例如 <quote>在子计划目标列表中找不到变量</quote>。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=bb65224aa214d11206ec63e55b3b560e -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [34740b90b] 2026-01-19 11:13:23 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [7650eabb6] 2026-01-19 11:14:51 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=11cff4e351a1070340ae55bc7efbea80 sig_cn_org=776af1d3829b20372cad624db12d8a10 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Avoid incorrect optimization when a subquery's grouping clause
      contains a volatile or set-returning function (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7650eabb6">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      当子查询的分组子句包含易变或返回集合的函数时，避免不
      正确的优化（Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7650eabb6">&sect;</ulink>
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=11cff4e351a1070340ae55bc7efbea80 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=54b467933534438771ca7c87e529ec83 sig_cn_org=28b5c3a2ca56267b6966db45ef08d906 source=18.3 
     <para>
      The planner was willing to push down outer-query restrictions
      referencing such a grouping column, leading to incorrect behavior
      due to multiple evaluation of a volatile function, or errors caused
      by introduction of a set-returning function into the
      subquery's <literal>WHERE</literal>/<literal>HAVING</literal>
      clauses.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      规划器愿意下推引用此分组列的外部查询限制，这导致由于
      多次评估易变函数而产生不正确的行为，或由于将返回集
      的函数引入到子查询的 <literal>WHERE</literal>/<literal>HAVING</literal>
      子句中而导致错误。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=54b467933534438771ca7c87e529ec83 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [559f9e90d] 2025-12-29 11:40:45 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [7e9f852a7] 2025-12-29 11:44:14 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=58ddf491f37e48bc96df0fea7addb699 sig_cn_org=3e93271f5715588048139150743bda39 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Look through PlaceHolderVar nodes when searching for statistics
      about an expression (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7e9f852a7">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在搜索表达式的统计信息时查看 PlaceHolderVar 节点
      （Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7e9f852a7">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=58ddf491f37e48bc96df0fea7addb699 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5bc34919b8dc6c8cad8cfaee8fc8119e sig_cn_org=1dd46ba06e806ca74c96a04ec2ef030e source=18.3 
     <para>
      This change allows the planner to find relevant statistics about
      expressions pulled up from subqueries or used in <literal>GROUP
      BY</literal>, avoiding falling back to a default estimate.
      (Arguably we should adjust any found statistics to account for an
      increased probability of the value being NULL, but we've never done
      the equivalent thing for plain Vars either.)  While this restriction
      is old, changes in <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> version 18
      made PlaceHolderVars more common than before, so make the change to
      avoid plan regressions in affected cases.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此更改允许规划器找到从子查询中提取或用于 <literal>GROUP
      BY</literal> 的表达式的相关统计信息，避免回退到默认估计。
      （可以说，我们应该调整任何找到的统计信息，以考虑值为
      NULL 的概率增加，但我们从未对普通 Vars 做过类似的事情。）
      尽管此限制较旧，但 <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 版本 18
      的更改使 PlaceHolderVars 比以前更常见，因此进行此更改以
      避免在受影响的情况下计划回归。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5bc34919b8dc6c8cad8cfaee8fc8119e -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [ad66f705f] 2025-12-29 11:38:49 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [b4cf74420] 2025-12-29 11:43:06 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e75af80d00492148605c15b5938c1ddc sig_cn_org=06c4b042c7970c4f5b0987754967ce90 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Look through no-op PlaceHolderVar nodes when matching expressions to
      indexes (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b4cf74420">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在匹配表达式到索引时查看无操作的 PlaceHolderVar 节点
      （Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;b4cf74420">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e75af80d00492148605c15b5938c1ddc -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8d3c4d0d29c6bbd368344281029e5d3c sig_cn_org=5fc562b9b26ae686f9692de5d556d249 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Because <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> version 18 uses
      PlaceHolderVars in more cases than before, some queries that
      formerly could use an index failed to do so.  Add logic to prevent
      that regression.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      因为 <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 版本 18 在更多情况下使用
      PlaceHolderVars，某些以前可以使用索引的查询未能做到这一点。
      添加逻辑以防止这种回归。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8d3c4d0d29c6bbd368344281029e5d3c -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
Branch: master [ed931377a] 2025-11-17 13:54:52 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [bf5b13a8a] 2025-11-17 13:55:26 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=98b237138d3605ea7319f305a713ea8f sig_cn_org=fbadb0b4bb6e526b643e026f9b948372 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix planner's conversion of <literal>OR</literal> clauses to
      ScalarArrayOp index conditions (Tender Wang, Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bf5b13a8a">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复规划器将 <literal>OR</literal> 子句转换为
      ScalarArrayOp 索引条件的问题（Tender Wang, Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bf5b13a8a">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=98b237138d3605ea7319f305a713ea8f -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6d464d634ba16f56687765dea9b84f12 sig_cn_org=7907168b044526b88eea2c65016f1956 source=18.3 
     <para>
      The code did not handle RelabelType nodes correctly, and could
      generate invalid expressions or fail to perform a valid conversion.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      代码未正确处理 RelabelType 节点，可能生成无效的表达式
      或未能执行有效的转换。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6d464d634ba16f56687765dea9b84f12 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
Branch: master [5528e8d10] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [a212877dc] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [e79b27662] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [b497766a8] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [f19502f04] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [9e77323fc] 2025-11-27 13:09:59 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f7601d6fab0a6355f7c764c6cb633571 sig_cn_org=610933869483df76155e0ee84434a2a2 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Allow indexscans on partial hash indexes even when the index's
      predicate implies the truth of the WHERE clause (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a212877dc">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      即使索引的谓词暗示 WHERE 子句的真实性，也允许对部分哈希
      索引进行索引扫描（Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a212877dc">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f7601d6fab0a6355f7c764c6cb633571 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8b882d3ca68475c3ef5f71269917f7f5 sig_cn_org=dbbe626f385ffd8cf0875a24b24f8648 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Normally we drop a WHERE clause that is implied by the predicate,
      since it's pointless to test it; it must hold for every index
      entry.  However that can prevent creation of an indexscan plan if
      the index is one that requires a WHERE clause on the leading index
      key, as hash indexes do.  Don't drop implied clauses when
      considering such an index.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      通常我们会删除由谓词暗示的 WHERE 子句，因为测试它是
      没有意义的；它必须对每个索引条目都成立。然而，这可能会
      阻止创建索引扫描计划，如果索引是需要在主索引键上有
      WHERE 子句的类型，如哈希索引。考虑此类索引时，不要删除
      隐含子句。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8b882d3ca68475c3ef5f71269917f7f5 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [951b60f7a] 2025-12-18 15:08:48 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [d77a5f981] 2025-12-18 15:09:26 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [4b6d096a0] 2025-12-18 15:09:23 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [a5277700e] 2025-12-18 15:09:21 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [460d97020] 2025-12-18 15:09:19 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [ab4256869] 2025-12-18 15:09:17 +0200
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dc293101a303bc0e4562e981a1ff4203 sig_cn_org=178f0823ab243623154170cc6ee531c6 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Do not emit WAL for unlogged BRIN indexes (Kirill Reshke)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d77a5f981">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      不为未记录的 BRIN 索引发出 WAL（Kirill Reshke）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d77a5f981">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dc293101a303bc0e4562e981a1ff4203 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=68ddbc3308dba58600802a82ee2ec703 sig_cn_org=bd6110e971caf27debb29e0bf5a72afb source=18.3 
     <para>
      One seldom-taken code path incorrectly emitted a WAL record
      relating to a BRIN index even if the index was marked unlogged.
      Crash recovery would then fail to replay that record, complaining
      that the file already exists.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      一条很少被采用的代码路径错误地发出了与 BRIN 索引相关的
      WAL 记录，即使该索引被标记为未记录。崩溃恢复将无法重放
      该记录，并抱怨文件已存在。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=68ddbc3308dba58600802a82ee2ec703 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Tomas Vondra <tomas.vondra@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [db14dcdec] 2026-01-26 20:05:17 +0100
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [eee71a66c] 2026-01-26 20:05:00 +0100
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=695d1029492e520aa904f10941dd6726 sig_cn_org=dab9458ed3e069c346990a002cc5f1be source=18.3 
     <para>
      Use the correct ordering function in parallel GIN index builds
      (Tomas Vondra)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;eee71a66c">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在并行 GIN 索引构建中使用正确的排序函数（Tomas Vondra）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;eee71a66c">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=695d1029492e520aa904f10941dd6726 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a03c30572d2981cb74cadcf8525fbaf7 sig_cn_org=87c657b29359ac0c659d430e67cde6ec source=18.3 
     <para>
      The parallel code used the default ordering operator (which is
      determined by the column data type's btree opclass), whereas it
      should use the ordering function specified by the GIN opclass, if
      any.  This led to a failure if the data type has no btree opclass,
      or to an invalid index if the opclass specifies an ordering function
      that doesn't agree with the btree opclass.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      并行代码使用了默认的排序运算符（由列数据类型的 btree
      opclass 决定），而应该使用 GIN opclass 指定的排序函数（如果有）。
      如果数据类型没有 btree opclass，这将导致失败；如果 opclass
      指定的排序函数与 btree opclass 不一致，则会导致无效的索引。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a03c30572d2981cb74cadcf8525fbaf7 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [8eeb4a0f7] 2025-11-12 20:59:36 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [321ec5462] 2025-11-12 21:00:42 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [d02c03ddc] 2025-11-12 21:01:13 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [053e1868b] 2025-11-12 21:01:42 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [1a469d7b5] 2025-11-12 21:02:12 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [eba917d36] 2025-11-12 21:02:36 +0200
Branch: master [797e9ea6e] 2025-11-12 20:59:44 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [7b069a187] 2025-11-12 21:00:46 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [c2682810a] 2025-11-12 21:01:16 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [44e8c60be] 2025-11-12 21:01:45 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [0c862646c] 2025-11-12 21:02:14 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [c2e58c071] 2025-11-12 21:02:38 +0200
Branch: master [0bdc777e8] 2025-11-12 21:19:03 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [82fa6b78d] 2025-11-12 21:26:58 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [d80d5f099] 2025-11-12 21:27:02 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [0e8eaa218] 2025-11-12 21:27:05 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [21a9014cf] 2025-11-12 21:27:07 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [84f1bf4af] 2025-11-12 21:27:11 +0200
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=037096a0184e481cea2658cb1256d7ec sig_cn_org=3975b40ed1f3210e0f3084a5d649c705 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Prevent truncation of CLOG that is still needed by
      unread <command>NOTIFY</command> messages (Joel Jacobson, Heikki
      Linnakangas)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;321ec5462">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7b069a187">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;82fa6b78d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      防止截断仍然被未读的 <command>NOTIFY</command> 消息所需的 CLOG
      （Joel Jacobson, Heikki Linnakangas）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;321ec5462">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7b069a187">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;82fa6b78d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=037096a0184e481cea2658cb1256d7ec -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5e664c1ac3f58808c674dd75a9c8a5e4 sig_cn_org=ae7b46d08aa92646bbeedb0ad87a7172 source=18.3 
     <para>
      This fix prevents <quote>could not access status of
      transaction</quote> errors when a backend is slow to
      absorb <command>NOTIFY</command> messages.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此修复防止在后端缓慢吸收 <command>NOTIFY</command> 消息时出现
      <quote>无法访问事务状态</quote> 错误。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5e664c1ac3f58808c674dd75a9c8a5e4 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [1b4699090] 2025-11-12 20:59:28 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [aab4a84bb] 2025-11-12 21:00:25 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [b821c9292] 2025-11-12 21:01:08 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [c1a5bde00] 2025-11-12 21:01:39 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [b1da37de2] 2025-11-12 21:02:07 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [7cb05dd2d] 2025-11-12 21:02:32 +0200
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e2b8d060ed9243182b0f99c58272fc7b sig_cn_org=446423c8c06fe3f54a457b442eb9d720 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Escalate errors occurring during <command>NOTIFY</command> message
      processing to FATAL, i.e. close the connection (Heikki Linnakangas)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;aab4a84bb">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在处理 <command>NOTIFY</command> 消息时，将发生的错误提升为 FATAL，
      即关闭连接（Heikki Linnakangas）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;aab4a84bb">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e2b8d060ed9243182b0f99c58272fc7b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d97be82a135e6e1a278617fa809354f3 sig_cn_org=f119e1de842e3f35cebfbe314fe1f63b source=18.3 
     <para>
      Formerly, if a backend got an error while absorbing
      a <command>NOTIFY</command> message, it would advance past that
      message, report the error to the client, and move on.  That behavior
      was fraught with problems though.  One big concern is that the
      client has no good way to know that a notification was lost, and
      certainly no way to know what was in it.  Depending on the
      application logic, missing a notification could cause the
      application to get stuck waiting, for example.  Also, any remaining
      messages would not get processed until someone sent a
      new <command>NOTIFY</command>.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      以前，如果后端在接收 <command>NOTIFY</command> 消息时发生错误，
      它会跳过该消息，向客户端报告错误，然后继续处理。
      然而，这种行为存在很多问题。一个主要问题是客户端无法
      确定通知是否丢失，当然也无法知道其中的内容。
      根据应用程序逻辑，错过通知可能会导致应用程序卡住等待。
      此外，任何剩余的消息都不会被处理，直到有人发送新的
      <command>NOTIFY</command>。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d97be82a135e6e1a278617fa809354f3 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0b484fa3d0e4331f9ef8cabd5540d141 sig_cn_org=83816f60e63b304182d67dd554c68e2d source=18.3 
     <para>
      Also, if the connection is idle at the time of receiving
      a <command>NOTIFY</command> signal, any ERROR would be escalated to
      FATAL anyway, due to unrelated concerns.  Therefore, we've chosen to
      make that happen in all cases, for consistency and to provide a
      clear signal to the application that it might have missed some
      notifications.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      此外，如果在接收 <command>NOTIFY</command> 信号时连接处于空闲状态，
      任何错误都会因无关的原因而提升为 FATAL。
      因此，我们选择在所有情况下都这样做，以保持一致性并向
      应用程序提供明确的信号，表明它可能错过了一些通知。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0b484fa3d0e4331f9ef8cabd5540d141 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
Branch: master [e217dc748] 2026-01-14 08:44:12 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [9c3caad02] 2026-01-14 08:44:52 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9936367f773f75fea51a7c0bdd44fc42 sig_cn_org=ea7faa413ca28d1246f7b88556f36754 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Consider grouping expressions when computing a query ID hash
      (Jian He)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9c3caad02">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在计算查询 ID 哈希时考虑分组表达式
      (Jian He)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9c3caad02">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9936367f773f75fea51a7c0bdd44fc42 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9690dd199ca4ffafb9c93e10851d36b8 sig_cn_org=2dd6fe027467b5337007fb28aff2b984 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Previously, two queries that were the same except in <literal>GROUP
      BY</literal> expressions would be merged
      by <filename>contrib/pg_stat_statements</filename> and other users
      of query IDs.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      之前，两个查询除了 <literal>GROUP BY</literal> 表达式不同外是相同的，
      会被 <filename>contrib/pg_stat_statements</filename> 和其他查询 ID 的用户合并。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9690dd199ca4ffafb9c93e10851d36b8 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Dean Rasheed <dean.a.rasheed@gmail.com>
Branch: master [1b92fe7bb] 2025-11-16 22:14:06 +0000
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [5749d95d4] 2025-11-16 22:15:10 +0000
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [d6c415c4b] 2025-11-16 22:15:45 +0000
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=38cde6dfe5c9f2d6bd7552e08091386b sig_cn_org=5c7d84a5f1aebe557f54ecba1119d39f source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix erroneous counting of updates in <command>EXPLAIN ANALYZE
      MERGE</command> with a concurrent update (Dean Rasheed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;5749d95d4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复在并发更新时 <command>EXPLAIN ANALYZE MERGE</command> 中
      更新计数错误的问题 (Dean Rasheed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;5749d95d4">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=38cde6dfe5c9f2d6bd7552e08091386b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3945374cf03fd708aeca5333113d4a67 sig_cn_org=64434a2060972adf4c45076ed4fb5508 source=18.3 
     <para>
      This situation led to an incorrect count of <quote>skipped</quote>
      tuples in <command>EXPLAIN</command>'s output, or to an assertion
      failure in an assert-enabled build.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      这种情况导致 <command>EXPLAIN</command> 输出中“跳过”的元组计数不正确，
      或在启用断言的构建中导致断言失败。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3945374cf03fd708aeca5333113d4a67 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [955f55068] 2025-12-23 13:37:16 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [3e3a80f62] 2025-12-23 13:37:23 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [bb87d7fef] 2025-12-23 13:37:25 +0200
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [7efef18ff] 2025-12-23 13:37:27 +0200
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [5d5487cd2] 2025-12-23 13:37:29 +0200
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [b6201c76e] 2025-12-23 13:37:31 +0200
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=34f2828adeaaaefe86a67a03e18c463d sig_cn_org=4db5420c2550d1e52f07c02d97d6a843 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix bug in following update chain when locking a tuple (Jasper
      Smit)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;3e3a80f62">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复在锁定元组时跟随更新链中的错误 (Jasper Smit)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;3e3a80f62">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=34f2828adeaaaefe86a67a03e18c463d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=df7c238e7c0b306179cc9e06981f79b3 sig_cn_org=2d344777f7a9bbb95700f471e0f3d2fd source=18.3 
     <para>
      This code path neglected to check the xmin of the first new tuple in
      the update chain, making it possible to lock an unrelated tuple if
      the original updater aborted and the space was immediately reclaimed
      by <command>VACUUM</command> and then re-used.
      That could cause unexpected transaction delays or deadlocks.
      Errors associated with having identified the wrong tuple have also
      been observed.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      该代码路径未能检查更新链中第一个新元组的 xmin，
      如果原始更新者中止并且空间被 <command>VACUUM</command> 立即回收并重新使用，
      则可能会锁定无关的元组。
      这可能导致意外的事务延迟或死锁。
      还观察到与识别错误元组相关的错误。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=df7c238e7c0b306179cc9e06981f79b3 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Robert Haas <rhaas@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [ecd275718] 2026-01-19 12:09:32 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [c80b0c9d6] 2026-01-19 12:09:48 -0500
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [ad569b54a] 2026-01-19 12:10:00 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5180f61782c4c5fa5deba20feaf9768f sig_cn_org=25865ac03bf44e7494c9445cba17ad64 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix incorrect handling of incremental backups of large tables
      (Robert Haas, Oleg Tkachenko)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c80b0c9d6">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复对大表增量备份的错误处理 (Robert Haas, Oleg Tkachenko)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c80b0c9d6">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5180f61782c4c5fa5deba20feaf9768f -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d356097e62413593fcece15fb33872fc sig_cn_org=f701dec41be9aefcd1af351920bcc4d8 source=18.3 
     <para>
      If a table exceeding 1GB (or in general, the installation's segment
      size) is truncated by <literal>VACUUM</literal> between the base
      backup and the incremental
      backup, <application>pg_combinebackup</application> could fail with
      an error about <quote>truncation block length in excess of segment
      size</quote>.  This prevented restoring the incremental backup.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      如果一个超过 1GB（或一般来说，安装的段大小）的表在基础备份和增量备份之间
      被 <literal>VACUUM</literal> 截断，<application>pg_combinebackup</application>
      可能会因“截断块长度超过段大小”的错误而失败。
      这阻止了增量备份的恢复。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d356097e62413593fcece15fb33872fc -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Amit Langote <amitlan@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [9cbb1d21d] 2026-01-16 13:02:42 +0900
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [1943ceb38] 2026-01-16 13:14:21 +0900
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [4071fe900] 2026-01-16 13:19:53 +0900
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [980b7c736] 2026-01-16 13:19:59 +0900
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [b926ff137] 2026-01-16 13:20:05 +0900
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [f6df78173] 2026-01-16 13:20:11 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8924ebdce2c11e07037d9d4df9bfdf94 sig_cn_org=c29dd5cf1ac6565772aff1fe2271f38b source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix potential backend process crash at process exit due to trying to
      release a lock in an already-unmapped shared memory segment
      (Rahila Syed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;1943ceb38">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复由于尝试在已经取消映射的共享内存段中释放锁而导致的后端进程崩溃
      (Rahila Syed)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;1943ceb38">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8924ebdce2c11e07037d9d4df9bfdf94 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Andres Freund <andres@anarazel.de>
Branch: master [807764990] 2026-01-15 11:09:07 -0500
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [7f1b3a4ce] 2026-01-15 11:09:49 -0500
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=b9a8ee602ef2e08a7a2987f667a3d8f6 sig_cn_org=b410e777f500f70e86389895982d8333 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix race condition in async I/O code (Andres Freund)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7f1b3a4ce">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复异步 I/O 代码中的竞争条件 (Andres Freund)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;7f1b3a4ce">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=b9a8ee602ef2e08a7a2987f667a3d8f6 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7bfb19a1fe1f30b4f86c3dd3f8265ccc sig_cn_org=79cd09123ae562343cc58e2eab66705f source=18.3 
     <para>
      It was possible for the result code of an asynchronous I/O operation
      to be overwritten before it was fetched.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      异步 I/O 操作的结果代码在获取之前可能被覆盖。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7bfb19a1fe1f30b4f86c3dd3f8265ccc -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Heikki Linnakangas <heikki.linnakangas@iki.fi>
Branch: master [102bdaa9b] 2026-01-15 16:48:45 +0200
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [09532a78b] 2026-01-15 16:49:42 +0200
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [d3ad4cef6] 2026-01-15 16:50:30 +0200
