-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9feb56ce172cf9322d319866c7983fc8 sig_cn_org=37ecd511f299c8ad95ea5c1d25aec79c source=18.3 
     <para>
      Fix incorrect configure probe
      for <function>io_uring_queue_init_mem()</function> (Masahiko Sawada)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;640772c6d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复 <function>io_uring_queue_init_mem()</function> 的
      不正确配置探测（Masahiko Sawada）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;640772c6d">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9feb56ce172cf9322d319866c7983fc8 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e171a48b82709a762b66c78e9653a180 sig_cn_org=48b66faf0489ea0028a5d9f7c9252dbc source=18.3 
     <para>
      This error resulted in failure to optimize async I/O buffer
      allocations in autotools-based builds, though the code did work when
      building with meson.  The main impact of the omission was
      slower-than-necessary backend process exits.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      该错误导致在基于 autotools 的构建中无法优化异步 I/O
      缓冲区分配，尽管在使用 meson 构建时代码可以正常工作。
      该遗漏的主要影响是后端进程退出速度比必要的要慢。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e171a48b82709a762b66c78e9653a180 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Thomas Munro <tmunro@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [f94e9141a] 2026-02-06 17:38:49 +1300
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [33e3de6d7] 2026-02-06 17:38:39 +1300
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [4dac22aa1] 2026-02-06 17:41:42 +1300
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [e37b59802] 2026-02-06 17:43:49 +1300
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=71bc0813fc207f8d033baf6aff34cd55 sig_cn_org=9ecfc635fb1ac4bb08e0b378b0c8c786 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Add new server parameter <xref linkend="guc-file-extend-method"/> to
      control use of <function>posix_fallocate()</function> (Thomas Munro)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;33e3de6d7">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      添加新的服务器参数 <xref linkend="guc-file-extend-method"/> 以
      控制使用 <function>posix_fallocate()</function>（Thomas Munro）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;33e3de6d7">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=71bc0813fc207f8d033baf6aff34cd55 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=efb3f4b88f6cfdfdfbc7bfb74b800cb4 sig_cn_org=6044fd5985feeb6ede8b37f4ffcf81aa source=18.3 
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> version 16 and later will
      use <function>posix_fallocate()</function>, if the platform provides
      it, to extend relation files.  However, this has been reported to
      interact poorly with some file systems: BTRFS compression is
      disabled by the use of <function>posix_fallocate()</function>, and
      XFS could produce spurious <literal>ENOSPC</literal> errors in older
      Linux kernel versions.  To provide a workaround, introduce this new
      server parameter.  Setting <varname>file_extend_method</varname>
      to <literal>write_zeros</literal> will cause the server to return to
      the old method of extending files by writing blocks of zeroes.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 版本 16 及更高版本将
      使用 <function>posix_fallocate()</function>，如果平台提供
      它，以扩展关系文件。然而，已报告此功能与某些文件系统
      的兼容性较差：使用 <function>posix_fallocate()</function> 会禁用
      BTRFS 压缩，并且 XFS 在较旧的 Linux 内核版本中可能会产生
      虚假的 <literal>ENOSPC</literal> 错误。为提供解决方法，引入
      这个新的服务器参数。将 <varname>file_extend_method</varname>
      设置为 <literal>write_zeros</literal> 将使服务器返回到
      通过写入零块来扩展文件的旧方法。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=efb3f4b88f6cfdfdfbc7bfb74b800cb4 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Thomas Munro <tmunro@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [c507ba55f] 2025-12-10 09:01:35 +1300
Branch: REL_18_STABLE [bebb281b0] 2025-12-10 09:05:21 +1300
