     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c7719315b9264bed81a157a3e17df1c3 -->
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-18">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0b073d207f2a6a5ff6853f3cc5510e02 sig_cn_org=3982a94f5f64860a06812c6e3fc9fde4 source=18.3 
  <title>Release 18</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布 18</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0b073d207f2a6a5ff6853f3cc5510e02 -->

  <formalpara>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda sig_cn_org=253305b4c6dff5b87ef36e3c2d95e52e source=15.7 
   <title>Release date:</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>发布日期：</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ee4241ed1a4ef8781805670e6923c71f sig_cn_org=f9171cd313742d86ad787324a570d3dc source=18.3 
   <para>2025-09-25</para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>2025-09-25</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ee4241ed1a4ef8781805670e6923c71f -->
  </formalpara>

  <sect2 id="release-18-highlights">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=13508788fd8dee2d1f9c928870e99338 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <title>Overview</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>概述</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=13508788fd8dee2d1f9c928870e99338 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9e2c32d9dc66eb9a6f751a895da34194 sig_cn_org=24ecb61e3d949b1ee69092a76cb800a8 source=18.3 
   <para>
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 contains many new features
    and enhancements, including:
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 包含许多新特性
    和增强功能，包括：
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9e2c32d9dc66eb9a6f751a895da34194 -->

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8c9c3eee534dc37ca087c3254807dfad sig_cn_org=7158c35ea316af13017d78a0a1f8eb6d source=18.3 
     <para>
      An asynchronous I/O (AIO) subsystem that can improve performance of
      sequential scans, bitmap heap scans, vacuums, and other operations.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      一个异步 I/O (AIO) 子系统，可以提高顺序扫描、位图堆扫描、
      清理和其他操作的性能。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8c9c3eee534dc37ca087c3254807dfad -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3c55a5da32ae401dc5d90c8e41974ce8 sig_cn_org=e171cad1322e022ac6ff080eaafe6e37 source=18.3 
     <para>
      <link linkend="pgupgrade"><application>pg_upgrade</application></link>
      now retains optimizer statistics.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <link linkend="pgupgrade"><application>pg_upgrade</application></link>
      现在保留优化器统计信息。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3c55a5da32ae401dc5d90c8e41974ce8 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5a3131a79f76141acd0c8fa86cb2e476 sig_cn_org=6e280a54593035a9d41a20ecd0bc66f0 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Support for "skip scan" lookups that allow using
      <link linkend="indexes-multicolumn">multicolumn B-tree indexes</link> in
      more cases.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      支持“跳过扫描”查找，允许在更多情况下使用
      <link linkend="indexes-multicolumn">多列 B-tree 索引</link>。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5a3131a79f76141acd0c8fa86cb2e476 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f1c373420fa034f4768e39e078e4d5e7 sig_cn_org=a4476385543cc9cf0a80d30bb7cb7f73 source=18.3 
     <para>
      <link linkend="func_uuid_gen_table"><function>uuidv7()</function></link>
      function for generating timestamp-ordered
      <link linkend="datatype-uuid">UUIDs</link>.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <link linkend="func_uuid_gen_table"><function>uuidv7()</function></link>
      函数用于生成时间戳排序的
      <link linkend="datatype-uuid">UUIDs</link>。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f1c373420fa034f4768e39e078e4d5e7 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6767a9c1c64c4acf181a28eed130e9be sig_cn_org=fd3486959a717602b25f0c13dbd3ea76 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Virtual
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-generated-stored">generated columns</link>
      that compute their values during read operations.  This is now the
      default for generated columns.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      虚拟
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-generated-stored">生成列</link>
      在读取操作期间计算其值。这现在是
      生成列的默认设置。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6767a9c1c64c4acf181a28eed130e9be -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ea8133f7cca1d94405a5e0d1999bf09b sig_cn_org=07b3ddd31816c47a839929e6dc607cbc source=18.3 
     <para>
      <link linkend="auth-oauth">OAuth authentication</link> support.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <link linkend="auth-oauth">OAuth 认证</link> 支持。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ea8133f7cca1d94405a5e0d1999bf09b -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ed6b7cf4aba378ea5d61a996c43a140d sig_cn_org=9d4c9367c6d80324d8b15d0b9916a801 source=18.3 
     <para>
      <literal>OLD</literal> and <literal>NEW</literal> support for
      <link linkend="dml-returning"><literal>RETURNING</literal></link> clauses
      in <xref linkend="sql-insert"/>, <xref linkend="sql-update"/>,
      <xref linkend="sql-delete"/>, and <xref linkend="sql-merge"/> commands.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <literal>OLD</literal> 和 <literal>NEW</literal> 支持
      <link linkend="dml-returning"><literal>RETURNING</literal></link> 子句
      在 <xref linkend="sql-insert"/>, <xref linkend="sql-update"/>,
      <xref linkend="sql-delete"/>, 和 <xref linkend="sql-merge"/> 命令中。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ed6b7cf4aba378ea5d61a996c43a140d -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ba1b68c3a5ec1f29c5992ad94ffdecbc sig_cn_org=a29c4021cf467b500e70ba93de0cb700 source=18.3 
     <para>
      Temporal constraints, or constraints over ranges, for
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-primary-key">PRIMARY KEY</link>,
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-unique">UNIQUE</link>, and
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-references">FOREIGN KEY</link>
      constraints.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      时间约束，或范围约束，用于
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-primary-key">主键</link>,
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-unique">唯一</link>, 和
      <link linkend="sql-createtable-parms-references">外键</link>
      约束。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ba1b68c3a5ec1f29c5992ad94ffdecbc -->
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d42c62d8fd1e3ee7a2c9a97fb21820fa sig_cn_org=3c9a64d0deec52799e5099d430f10f63 source=18.3 
   <para>
    The above items and other new features of
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 are explained in more detail
    in the sections below.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    上述项目和其他新特性在
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 中的详细说明
    在下面的章节中。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d42c62d8fd1e3ee7a2c9a97fb21820fa -->

  </sect2>

  <sect2  id="release-18-migration">

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ce54655c26f17e6b85e1b2d152bc9239 sig_cn_org=7ff68a8c4ecb7c1d7fd11b942eded0f7 source=18.3 
   <title>Migration to Version 18</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 18</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ce54655c26f17e6b85e1b2d152bc9239 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5b9f61db6c635ea82b92aa17abd61182 sig_cn_org=186150cca28661dd1b0ab789cfdf3f47 source=16.8 
   <para>
    A dump/restore using <xref linkend="app-pg-dumpall"/> or use of
    <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/> or logical replication is required for
    those wishing to migrate data from any previous release.  See <xref
    linkend="upgrading"/> for general information on migrating to new
    major releases.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    需要使用<xref linkend="app-pg-dumpall"/>进行转储/恢复，或者使用
    <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/>或逻辑复制来迁移数据，以从任何先前版本迁移。
    有关迁移到新主要版本的一般信息，请参阅<xref linkend="upgrading"/>。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5b9f61db6c635ea82b92aa17abd61182 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=bcc433ef876d182fd3f7172cccc58ae4 sig_cn_org=602ef6d6800a36c359b3023d12850f83 source=18.3 
   <para>
    Version 18 contains a number of changes that may affect compatibility
    with previous releases.  Observe the following incompatibilities:
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    版本 18 包含一些可能影响与
    以前版本兼容性的更改。请注意以下不兼容性：
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=bcc433ef876d182fd3f7172cccc58ae4 -->

   <itemizedlist>

<!--
Author: Peter Eisentraut <peter@eisentraut.org>
2024-10-16 [04bec894a04] initdb: Change default to using data checksums.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5d93072963093250d955a48ebcff48c8 sig_cn_org=ad91a917a52fff8a99591d759520cb5f source=18.3 
    <para>
    Change <xref linkend="app-initdb"/> default to enable data checksums
    (Greg Sabino Mullane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;04bec894a04">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    更改 <xref linkend="app-initdb"/> 默认以启用数据校验和
    (Greg Sabino Mullane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;04bec894a04">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5d93072963093250d955a48ebcff48c8 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d5a718a185a7b9649eac12f58e4efaf8 sig_cn_org=691cb434f3b95133030caaa1d44390ca source=18.3 
    <para>
    Checksums can be disabled with the
    new <application>initdb</application> option
    <option>-&minus;no-data-checksums</option>.  <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/>
    requires matching cluster checksum settings, so this new option can
    be useful to upgrade non-checksum old clusters.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    可以使用新的 <application>initdb</application> 选项
    <option>--no-data-checksums</option> 禁用校验和。<xref linkend="pgupgrade"/>
    需要匹配的集群校验和设置，因此这个新选项可以
    用于升级不带校验和的旧集群。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d5a718a185a7b9649eac12f58e4efaf8 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2025-01-16 [d7674c9fa] Seek zone abbreviations in the IANA data before timezone
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f5fd92d03959e88d9592d017bc13f697 sig_cn_org=a9b76824fa603a25e90c2a5e1630f770 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Change time zone abbreviation handling (Tom Lane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d7674c9fa">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    更改时区缩写处理 (Tom Lane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d7674c9fa">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f5fd92d03959e88d9592d017bc13f697 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=fb8b1b8981d13328e28b8e546c7fc068 sig_cn_org=0022b53b05eb351577b5e9eda995c03d source=18.3 
    <para>
    The system will now favor the current session's time
    zone abbreviations before checking the server variable
    <xref linkend="guc-timezone-abbreviations"/>. Previously
    <varname>timezone_abbreviations</varname> was checked first.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    系统现在将优先考虑当前会话的时区
    缩写，然后再检查服务器变量
    <xref linkend="guc-timezone-abbreviations"/>。之前
    <varname>timezone_abbreviations</varname> 是首先检查的。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=fb8b1b8981d13328e28b8e546c7fc068 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Nathan Bossart <nathan@postgresql.org>
2024-12-02 [db6a4a985] Deprecate MD5 passwords.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=935499854af4e805baecd38e08724cac sig_cn_org=9dafc184e6c64aac989934093689b982 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Deprecate <link linkend="auth-password">MD5 password</link>
    authentication (Nathan Bossart)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;db6a4a985">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    弃用 <link linkend="auth-password">MD5 密码</link>
    认证 (Nathan Bossart)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;db6a4a985">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=935499854af4e805baecd38e08724cac -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c9b33018ccda11b60b019180e08df936 sig_cn_org=76a95e35a62c0514da39038c7f55f807 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Support for MD5 passwords will be removed in a future major
    version release.  <xref linkend="sql-createrole"/> and <xref
    linkend="sql-alterrole"/> now emit deprecation warnings when
    setting MD5 passwords.  These warnings can be disabled by setting
    the <xref linkend="guc-md5-password-warnings"/> parameter to
    <literal>off</literal>.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    对 MD5 密码的支持将在未来的主要
    版本发布中移除。<xref linkend="sql-createrole"/> 和 <xref
    linkend="sql-alterrole"/> 在设置 MD5 密码时现在会发出弃用警告。
    通过将 <xref linkend="guc-md5-password-warnings"/> 参数设置为
    <literal>off</literal> 可以禁用这些警告。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c9b33018ccda11b60b019180e08df936 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-09-24 [62ddf7ee9] Add ONLY support for VACUUM and ANALYZE
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c936ee4f53fe9ca85e3c710f869c3af0 sig_cn_org=bebc4000efd394ee9fbbbd73a7aff494 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Change <xref linkend="sql-vacuum"/> and <xref linkend="sql-analyze"/>
    to process the inheritance children of a parent (Michael Harris)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;62ddf7ee9">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    更改 <xref linkend="sql-vacuum"/> 和 <xref linkend="sql-analyze"/>
    以处理父级的继承子项 (Michael Harris)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;62ddf7ee9">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c936ee4f53fe9ca85e3c710f869c3af0 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=11196a4895fd57d23aff36313b6173b6 sig_cn_org=92dc2b80eed34f3f35c7b049760ef148 source=18.3 
    <para>
    The previous behavior can be performed by using the new
    <literal>ONLY</literal> option.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    之前的行为可以通过使用新的
    <literal>ONLY</literal> 选项来实现。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=11196a4895fd57d23aff36313b6173b6 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2024-09-30 [770233748] Do not treat \. as an EOF marker in CSV mode for COPY IN
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2024-10-01 [da8a4c166] Reject a copy EOF marker that has data ahead of it on th
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3f32106517462fb780ba32d416cfd19c sig_cn_org=e6b4bd7255905274f0935ac4c9175270 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Prevent <link linkend="sql-copy"><command>COPY FROM</command></link>
    from treating <literal>\.</literal> as an end-of-file marker when
    reading <acronym>CSV</acronym> files (Daniel Vérité, Tom Lane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;770233748">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;da8a4c166">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    防止 <link linkend="sql-copy"><command>COPY FROM</command></link>
    在读取 <acronym>CSV</acronym> 文件时将 <literal>\.</literal> 视为
    文件结束标记 (Daniel Vérité, Tom Lane)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;770233748">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;da8a4c166">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3f32106517462fb780ba32d416cfd19c -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e75911f6b94bc8ef44ce689c23f97793 sig_cn_org=75933fbba4cbf2e24fbd2c1e282a3c78 source=18.3 
    <para>
    <xref linkend="app-psql"/> will still treat
    <literal>\.</literal> as an end-of-file marker when reading
    <acronym>CSV</acronym> files from <literal>STDIN</literal>.
    Older <application>psql</application> clients connecting to
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 servers might experience <link
    linkend="app-psql-meta-commands-copy"><literal>\copy</literal></link>
    problems.  This release also enforces that <literal>\.</literal>
    must appear alone on a line.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    <xref linkend="app-psql"/> 在从 <literal>STDIN</literal> 读取
    <acronym>CSV</acronym> 文件时仍将 <literal>\.</literal> 视为
    文件结束标记。连接到 <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18
    服务器的旧版 <application>psql</application> 客户端可能会遇到
    <link linkend="app-psql-meta-commands-copy"><literal>\copy</literal></link>
    问题。此版本还强制要求 <literal>\.</literal> 必须单独出现在一行上。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e75911f6b94bc8ef44ce689c23f97793 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
2024-10-03 [e2bab2d79] Remove support for unlogged on partitioned tables
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=4b3e532db4550785051c7a6e0e0da47a sig_cn_org=9607e08e522ec4136d04b0316fb689e5 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Disallow unlogged partitioned tables (Michael Paquier)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e2bab2d79">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    不允许无日志分区表 (Michael Paquier)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e2bab2d79">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=4b3e532db4550785051c7a6e0e0da47a -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=b64e2c97ecdfdde964a2760b5983d60a sig_cn_org=41cd26dec0846efadb81554ddeab8c96 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Previously <link linkend="sql-altertable"><command>ALTER TABLE SET
    [UN]LOGGED</command></link> did nothing, and the creation of an
    unlogged partitioned table did not cause its children to be unlogged.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    之前 <link linkend="sql-altertable"><command>ALTER TABLE SET
    [UN]LOGGED</command></link> 没有任何作用，创建无日志分区表
    并不会导致其子表也变为无日志。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=b64e2c97ecdfdde964a2760b5983d60a -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2025-01-23 [01463e1cc] Ensure that AFTER triggers run as the instigating user.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e683ba588671ef891ce40c6bedaff1f9 sig_cn_org=3bf86f65efab8bee6f1e5d1734401bf7 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Execute <literal>AFTER</literal> <link
    linkend="triggers">triggers</link> as the role that was active when
    trigger events were queued (Laurenz Albe)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;01463e1cc">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    作为在触发器事件排队时处于活动状态的角色执行 <literal>AFTER</literal>
    <link linkend="triggers">触发器</link> (Laurenz Albe)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;01463e1cc">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e683ba588671ef891ce40c6bedaff1f9 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3e15d05fc84d3481977d0d0b295c40e5 sig_cn_org=c3cd670221b33246cd3fd87994a65c70 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Previously such triggers were run as the role that was active at
    trigger execution time (e.g., at <xref linkend="sql-commit"/>).
    This is significant for cases where the role is changed between queue
    time and transaction commit.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    之前此类触发器是在触发器执行时处于活动状态的角色下运行
    (例如，在 <xref linkend="sql-commit"/> 时)。这在角色在排队时间
    和事务提交之间发生变化的情况下是重要的。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3e15d05fc84d3481977d0d0b295c40e5 -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Fujii Masao <fujii@postgresql.org>
2024-09-12 [fefa76f70] Remove old RULE privilege completely.
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3179de2cc5499b0d1e245c8080b8d87d sig_cn_org=78b519b3d0e6d8de31a67f56fc54b99a source=18.3 
    <para>
    Remove non-functional support for rule privileges in <xref
    linkend="sql-grant"/>/<xref linkend="sql-revoke"/> (Fujii Masao)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fefa76f70">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    移除 <xref linkend="sql-grant"/>/<xref linkend="sql-revoke"/> 中
    对规则权限的非功能性支持 (Fujii Masao)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fefa76f70">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3179de2cc5499b0d1e245c8080b8d87d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=34bf5359d9f7dc85aa8fb2d4c52ac13c sig_cn_org=33fac3a795a7dfdc4e6764da3fe2b1ab source=18.3 
    <para>
    These have been non-functional since
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 8.2.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    自 <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 8.2 以来，这些功能一直没有
    功能。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=34bf5359d9f7dc85aa8fb2d4c52ac13c -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-08-12 [f0d112759] Remove "parent" column from pg_backend_memory_contexts
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c472a4e41a62f165ddf2db4e1fc33954 sig_cn_org=696f1c61aa4e7970917b6a6687b78e39 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Remove column <link
    linkend="view-pg-backend-memory-contexts"><structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname></link>.<structfield>parent</structfield>
    (Melih Mutlu)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f0d112759">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    移除列 <link
    linkend="view-pg-backend-memory-contexts"><structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname></link>.<structfield>parent</structfield>
    (Melih Mutlu)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f0d112759">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c472a4e41a62f165ddf2db4e1fc33954 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=67ddc1784346c3451574b6153417f50f sig_cn_org=4ca400ae8e320fb6efc165f22bc5dfc3 source=18.3 
    <para>
    This is no longer needed since
    <structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname>.<structfield>path</structfield>
    was added.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    由于添加了 <structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname>.<structfield>path</structfield>
    ，这不再需要。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=67ddc1784346c3451574b6153417f50f -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-07-25 [32d3ed816] Add path column to pg_backend_memory_contexts view
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2025-04-18 [d9e03864b] Make levels 1-based in
    pg_log_backend_memory_contexts()
Author: Fujii Masao <fujii@postgresql.org>
2025-04-21 [706cbed35] doc: Fix memory context level in pg_log_backend_memory_c
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=383d405bf097e5d491bdeda384daaa91 sig_cn_org=aedc10372c7b98a6df95d8f1b71cd301 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Change
    <structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname>.<structfield>level</structfield>
    and <link
    linkend="functions-admin-signal-table"><function>pg_log_backend_memory_contexts()</function></link>
    to be one-based (Melih Mutlu, Atsushi Torikoshi, David Rowley,
    Fujii Masao)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;32d3ed816">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d9e03864b">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;706cbed35">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    将 <structname>pg_backend_memory_contexts</structname>.<structfield>level</structfield>
    和 <link
    linkend="functions-admin-signal-table"><function>pg_log_backend_memory_contexts()</function></link>
    更改为从 1 开始 (Melih Mutlu, Atsushi Torikoshi, David Rowley,
    Fujii Masao)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;32d3ed816">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;d9e03864b">&sect;</ulink>
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;706cbed35">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=383d405bf097e5d491bdeda384daaa91 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a138752b0778223910be4c78154fe87e sig_cn_org=fbb4edde71e8e00b0550f2267a15b999 source=18.3 
    <para>
    These were previously zero-based.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    之前这些是从 0 开始的。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a138752b0778223910be4c78154fe87e -->
    </listitem>

<!--
Author: Peter Eisentraut <peter@eisentraut.org>
2024-12-17 [fb1a18810f0] Remove ts_locale.c's lowerstr()
-->

    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8c95e3ca500c26ba3d99bb656689612c sig_cn_org=6f347cd71f052b0189fffec3c725b727 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Change <link linkend="textsearch">full text search</link> to use the
    default collation provider of the cluster to read configuration files
    and dictionaries, rather than always using libc (Peter Eisentraut)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fb1a18810f0">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    更改 <link linkend="textsearch">全文搜索</link> 以使用集群的默认
    排序提供程序来读取配置文件和字典，而不是始终使用 libc
    (Peter Eisentraut)
    <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fb1a18810f0">&sect;</ulink>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8c95e3ca500c26ba3d99bb656689612c -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5c45b775a4eb8ffa1053d8799a2af216 sig_cn_org=4daa9188b4a2171dd1f9d3edfd45b875 source=18.3 
    <para>
    Clusters that default to non-libc collation providers (e.g., ICU,
    builtin) that behave differently than libc for characters processed
    by LC_CTYPE could observe changes in behavior of some full-text
    search functions, as well as the <xref linkend="pgtrgm"/> extension.
    When upgrading such clusters using <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/>, it
    is recommended to reindex all indexes related to full-text search
    and <application>pg_trgm</application> after the upgrade.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
    默认使用非 libc 排序提供程序的集群 (例如，ICU，
    内置) 对于由 LC_CTYPE 处理的字符，其行为可能与 libc 不同，
    可能会观察到某些全文搜索函数的行为变化，以及 <xref linkend="pgtrgm"/> 扩展。
    在使用 <xref linkend="pgupgrade"/> 升级此类集群时，建议在升级后
    重新索引与全文搜索和 <application>pg_trgm</application> 相关的所有索引。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5c45b775a4eb8ffa1053d8799a2af216 -->
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="release-18-changes">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b sig_cn_org=f104d50dd9d4dd802f94229ebe5bc097 source=15.7 
   <title>Changes</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>变更</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=08125176c43484bf2f94284125cd7686 sig_cn_org=703abf943bab444773418fd6cf93d855 source=18.3 
    <para>
     Below you will find a detailed account of the changes between
    <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18 and the previous major
    release.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
     在这里您将找到关于 <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 18
    与之前主要版本之间变化的详细说明。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=08125176c43484bf2f94284125cd7686 -->

   <sect3 id="release-18-server">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9189294b7a121aae803ff469797ca246 sig_cn_org=d9be102ccf075d32052f6a1c47f345a9 source=15.7 
    <title>Server</title>
________________________________________________________-->
    <title>服务器</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9189294b7a121aae803ff469797ca246 -->

    <sect4 id="release-18-optimizer">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=74b6eff57a1f8c0e207b184771081be9 sig_cn_org=9a948b44ad66c389427f923daffd016d source=15.7 
     <title>Optimizer</title>
________________________________________________________-->
     <title>优化器</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=74b6eff57a1f8c0e207b184771081be9 -->

     <itemizedlist>

<!--
Author: Alexander Korotkov <akorotkov@postgresql.org>
2025-02-17 [fc069a3a6] Implement Self-Join Elimination
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=01cbe942b619d183e09a2b9326acaa7c sig_cn_org=9443d46ce8c7e55aab432d1fee3a5591 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Automatically remove some unnecessary table self-joins (Andrey
      Lepikhov, Alexander Kuzmenkov, Alexander Korotkov, Alena Rybakina)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fc069a3a6">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      自动移除一些不必要的表自连接（Andrey Lepikhov,
      Alexander Kuzmenkov, Alexander Korotkov, Alena Rybakina）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;fc069a3a6">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=01cbe942b619d183e09a2b9326acaa7c -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=b3bb9e6bf88c2eab861141b65d3753ed sig_cn_org=b70ae99cfc85cb2a20a913a04dfbbebe source=18.3 
      <para>
      This optimization can be disabled using server variable <xref
      linkend="guc-enable-self-join-elimination"/>.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      此优化可以通过服务器变量 <xref
      linkend="guc-enable-self-join-elimination"/> 禁用。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=b3bb9e6bf88c2eab861141b65d3753ed -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Alexander Korotkov <akorotkov@postgresql.org>
2025-04-04 [c0962a113] Convert 'x IN (VALUES ...)' to 'x = ANY ...' then approp
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3f81cb77a00684e2574cd58214cbfc38 sig_cn_org=2b9c41e26eae422103ce3d682e6ce501 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Convert some <link
      linkend="functions-comparisons-in-scalar"><literal>IN (VALUES
      ...)</literal></link> to <literal>x = ANY ...</literal> for better
      optimizer statistics (Alena Rybakina, Andrei Lepikhov)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c0962a113">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      将一些 <link
      linkend="functions-comparisons-in-scalar"><literal>IN (VALUES
      ...)</literal></link> 转换为 <literal>x = ANY ...</literal> 以获得
      更好的优化器统计信息（Alena Rybakina, Andrei Lepikhov）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c0962a113">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3f81cb77a00684e2574cd58214cbfc38 -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Alexander Korotkov <akorotkov@postgresql.org>
2024-11-24 [ae4569161] Teach bitmap path generation about transforming OR-claus
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3398c8aec9dc077e22669faaaeddfea1 sig_cn_org=1db77cf3cdd8d3d75210a3910a8a21a7 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Allow transforming <link
      linkend="functions-logical"><literal>OR</literal></link>-clauses
      to arrays for faster index processing (Alexander Korotkov, Andrey
      Lepikhov)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ae4569161">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      允许将 <link
      linkend="functions-logical"><literal>OR</literal></link> 子句
      转换为数组，以加快索引处理速度（Alexander Korotkov,
      Andrey Lepikhov）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ae4569161">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3398c8aec9dc077e22669faaaeddfea1 -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2024-09-10 [52c707483] Use a hash table to de-duplicate column names in ruleuti
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2024-12-19 [276279295] Convert SetOp to read its inputs as outerPlan and innerP
Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2024-12-19 [8d96f57d5] Improve planner's handling of SetOp plans.
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-09-05 [908a96861] Optimize WindowAgg's use of tuplestores
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6abbbc300ac27b8cc067cab66638c903 sig_cn_org=3132745272497a8b6c559bc53af73fe4 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Speed up the processing of <link
      linkend="sql-intersect"><literal>INTERSECT</literal></link>,
      <link linkend="sql-except"><literal>EXCEPT</literal></link>, <link
      linkend="tutorial-window">window aggregates</link>, and <link
      linkend="sql-createview">view column aliases</link> (Tom Lane,
      David Rowley)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;52c707483">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;276279295">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;8d96f57d5">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;908a96861">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      加快 <link
      linkend="sql-intersect"><literal>INTERSECT</literal></link>,
      <link linkend="sql-except"><literal>EXCEPT</literal></link>, <link
      linkend="tutorial-window">窗口聚合</link> 和 <link
      linkend="sql-createview">视图列别名</link> 的处理速度（Tom Lane,
      David Rowley）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;52c707483">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;276279295">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;8d96f57d5">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;908a96861">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6abbbc300ac27b8cc067cab66638c903 -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
2024-11-26 [a8ccf4e93] Reordering DISTINCT keys to match input path's pathkeys
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e6a0e561579011c3385d8d6b66a56eee sig_cn_org=e6ad4841b06a67790d94a4091486b929 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Allow the keys of <link linkend="sql-distinct"><command>SELECT
      DISTINCT</command></link> to be internally reordered to avoid sorting
      (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a8ccf4e93">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      允许 <link linkend="sql-distinct"><command>SELECT
      DISTINCT</command></link> 的键在内部重新排序以避免排序
      （Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a8ccf4e93">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e6a0e561579011c3385d8d6b66a56eee -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=95bb4b4bcd111344edacd00c9c6411aa sig_cn_org=8a7a483b852426d30b01afea6ea4e46f source=18.3 
      <para>
      This optimization can be disabled using <xref
      linkend="guc-enable-distinct-reordering"/>.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      此优化可以通过 <xref
      linkend="guc-enable-distinct-reordering"/> 禁用。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=95bb4b4bcd111344edacd00c9c6411aa -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-12-12 [bd10ec529] Detect redundant GROUP BY columns using UNIQUE indexes
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3c1afe268032cdb824d7808c00ec3a82 sig_cn_org=698cb96524cce3fd4278ae6fc629b568 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Ignore <link linkend="sql-groupby"><literal>GROUP BY</literal></link>
      columns that are functionally dependent on other columns (Zhang
      Mingli, Jian He, David Rowley)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bd10ec529">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      忽略与其他列功能依赖的 <link linkend="sql-groupby"><literal>GROUP BY</literal></link>
      列（Zhang Mingli, Jian He, David Rowley）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;bd10ec529">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3c1afe268032cdb824d7808c00ec3a82 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dbfab3a412720f3ee4265b2ea3b9b12e sig_cn_org=ea7d36ae9eafdeaf3fc5cb8751d73927 source=18.3 
      <para>
      If a <literal>GROUP BY</literal> clause includes all columns of
      a unique index, as well as other columns of the same table, those
      other columns are redundant and can be dropped from the grouping.
      This was already true for non-deferred primary keys.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      如果 <literal>GROUP BY</literal> 子句包含唯一索引的所有列，以及同一表的其他列，
      则这些其他列是多余的，可以从分组中删除。这对于非延迟主键已经成立。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dbfab3a412720f3ee4265b2ea3b9b12e -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
2024-10-09 [67a54b9e8] Allow pushdown of HAVING clauses with grouping sets
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
2024-09-10 [247dea89f] Introduce an RTE for the grouping step
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
2024-09-10 [f5050f795] Mark expressions nullable by grouping sets
Author: Richard Guo <rguo@postgresql.org>
2025-03-13 [cc5d98525] Fix incorrect handling of subquery pullup
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=626b664ee3a14bac355708a6baa361b5 sig_cn_org=d02e3c8a3b2a1d5cb8463296ffb2ea1b source=18.3 
      <para>
      Allow some <link
      linkend="sql-having"><literal>HAVING</literal></link> clauses
      on <link linkend="queries-grouping-sets"><literal>GROUPING
      SETS</literal></link> to be pushed to <link
      linkend="sql-where"><literal>WHERE</literal></link> clauses
      (Richard Guo)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;67a54b9e8">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;247dea89f">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f5050f795">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;cc5d98525">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      允许一些 <link
      linkend="sql-having"><literal>HAVING</literal></link> 子句
      在 <link linkend="queries-grouping-sets"><literal>GROUPING
      SETS</literal></link> 上被推送到 <link
      linkend="sql-where"><literal>WHERE</literal></link> 子句
      （Richard Guo）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;67a54b9e8">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;247dea89f">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;f5050f795">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;cc5d98525">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=626b664ee3a14bac355708a6baa361b5 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0feabba5c5e7e009a21fd076377b4df8 sig_cn_org=b8d6be2b5b840ca7f1377f44c7eb4bf7 source=18.3 
      <para>
      This allows earlier row filtering.  This release also fixes some
      <literal>GROUPING SETS</literal> queries that used to return
      incorrect results.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      这允许更早的行过滤。此版本还修复了一些以前返回
      不正确结果的 <literal>GROUPING SETS</literal> 查询。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0feabba5c5e7e009a21fd076377b4df8 -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: David Rowley <drowley@postgresql.org>
2024-07-09 [036bdcec9] Teach planner how to estimate rows for timestamp generat
Author: Dean Rasheed <dean.a.rasheed@gmail.com>
2024-12-02 [97173536e] Add a planner support function for numeric generate_seri
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1cce1ba246b0be315137c92a04f90280 sig_cn_org=4f902421128ea5d44afb0081efa372aa source=18.3 
      <para>
      Improve row estimates for <link
      linkend="functions-srf-series"><function>generate_series()</function></link>
      using <link linkend="datatype-numeric"><type>numeric</type></link>
      and <link linkend="datatype-datetime"><type>timestamp</type></link>
      values (David Rowley, Song Jinzhou)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;036bdcec9">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;97173536e">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      改进 <link
      linkend="functions-srf-series"><function>generate_series()</function></link>
      的行估算，使用 <link linkend="datatype-numeric"><type>numeric</type></link>
      和 <link linkend="datatype-datetime"><type>timestamp</type></link>
      值（David Rowley, Song Jinzhou）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;036bdcec9">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;97173536e">&sect;</ulink>
