      Add column <link
      linkend="monitoring-pg-stat-checkpointer-view"><structname>pg_stat_checkpointer</structname></link>.<structfield>num_done</structfield>
      to report the number of completed checkpoints (Anton A. Melnikov)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;559efce1d">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      添加列 <link
      linkend="monitoring-pg-stat-checkpointer-view"><structname>pg_stat_checkpointer</structname></link>.<structfield>num_done</structfield>
      以报告已完成的检查点数量（Anton A. Melnikov）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;559efce1d">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dafc75fe5b8597e41d8cb157925d7050 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=bb3fe7bf80e7df2750c0cc5cf574c75f sig_cn_org=063bf8b237c930071e213ce9f7d5f42c source=18.3 
      <para>
      Columns <structfield>num_timed</structfield> and
      <structfield>num_requested</structfield> count both completed and
      skipped checkpoints.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      列 <structfield>num_timed</structfield> 和
      <structfield>num_requested</structfield> 统计已完成和
      跳过的检查点数量。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=bb3fe7bf80e7df2750c0cc5cf574c75f -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Fujii Masao <fujii@postgresql.org>
2024-10-02 [17cc5f666] Fix inconsistent reporting of checkpointer stats.
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=dfb7f5ef518c70e3bdeb4d209cc592a1 sig_cn_org=828014be4220f3f7876a97b377ee7b69 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Add column
      <structname>pg_stat_checkpointer</structname>.<structfield>slru_written</structfield>
      to report <acronym>SLRU</acronym> buffers written (Nitin Jadhav)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;17cc5f666">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      添加列
      <structname>pg_stat_checkpointer</structname>.<structfield>slru_written</structfield>
      以报告已写入的 <acronym>SLRU</acronym> 缓冲区数量（Nitin Jadhav）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;17cc5f666">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=dfb7f5ef518c70e3bdeb4d209cc592a1 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6b16e150c8a49a803719a81855441c30 sig_cn_org=b7819cc2bbaaabe3d047408428fe948b source=18.3 
      <para>
      Also, modify the checkpoint server log message to report separate
      shared buffer and <acronym>SLRU</acronym> buffer values.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      此外，修改检查点服务器日志消息以报告单独的
      共享缓冲区和 <acronym>SLRU</acronym> 缓冲区值。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6b16e150c8a49a803719a81855441c30 -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
2024-11-11 [e7a9496de] Add two attributes to pg_stat_database for parallel work
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=53c6a7d3683c5088ffacebf3df7796e0 sig_cn_org=fc2723d85ab08656c1a65b0e03722b13 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Add columns to <link
      linkend="monitoring-pg-stat-database-view"><structname>pg_stat_database</structname></link>
      to report parallel worker activity (Benoit Lobréau)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e7a9496de">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      向 <link
      linkend="monitoring-pg-stat-database-view"><structname>pg_stat_database</structname></link>
      添加列以报告并行工作者活动（Benoit Lobréau）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;e7a9496de">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=53c6a7d3683c5088ffacebf3df7796e0 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ab2b53415dcf95c445e25152f1ea3b1e sig_cn_org=6a8ec245cf4d4a4020d41c5f75538f34 source=18.3 
      <para>
      The new columns are
      <structfield>parallel_workers_to_launch</structfield> and
      <structfield>parallel_workers_launched</structfield>.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      新列为
      <structfield>parallel_workers_to_launch</structfield> 和
      <structfield>parallel_workers_launched</structfield>。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ab2b53415dcf95c445e25152f1ea3b1e -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Álvaro Herrera <alvherre@alvh.no-ip.org>
2025-03-18 [62d712ecf] Introduce squashing of constant lists in query jumbling
Author: Álvaro Herrera <alvherre@alvh.no-ip.org>
2025-03-27 [9fbd53dea] Remove the query_id_squash_values GUC
Author: Álvaro Herrera <alvherre@kurilemu.de>
Branch: master Release: REL_18_BR [c2da1a5d6] 2025-06-24 19:36:32 +0200
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=bc41856c59e17ae68204424db22a1fb6 sig_cn_org=d29ccd06ce4d62c306ddf9b41c144a39 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Have <link linkend="guc-compute-query-id">query id</link> computation
      of constant lists consider only the first and last constants (Dmitry
      Dolgov, Sami Imseih)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;62d712ecf">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9fbd53dea">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c2da1a5d6">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      使 <link linkend="guc-compute-query-id">查询 ID</link> 的计算
      仅考虑第一个和最后一个常量（Dmitry
      Dolgov, Sami Imseih）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;62d712ecf">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;9fbd53dea">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;c2da1a5d6">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=bc41856c59e17ae68204424db22a1fb6 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e4f358fb5326f067123656f6689e569a sig_cn_org=12860fabec2eaab9cab3744282f808a4 source=18.3 
      <para>
      Jumbling is used by <xref linkend="pgstatstatements"/>.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
      颠倒顺序由 <xref linkend="pgstatstatements"/> 使用。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e4f358fb5326f067123656f6689e569a -->
      </listitem>

<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
2025-03-26 [787514b30] Use relation name instead of OID in query jumbling for R
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c755b2bbe3f6f7437a83416a1b316ba3 sig_cn_org=60211b793f142cc6f7aea44f803f78df source=18.3 
      <para>
      Adjust query id computations to group together queries using the
      same relation name (Michael Paquier, Sami Imseih)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;787514b30">&sect;</ulink>
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
